{"questionId":"21407","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A game is played where two unbiased dice are rolled and the score in the game is the&nbsp;greater of the two numbers shown. If the two numbers are the same, then the score in the&nbsp;game is the number shown on one of the dice. A diagram showing the possible outcomes is&nbsp;given below.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/f29e27dfdfd95e6f383c459d1be41d4a81fb87a3.png\"></p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> be the random variable “the score in a game”.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Find the probability that</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>a player scores at least <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> in a game.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>32</mn><mn>36</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>888888</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>88</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21407","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.10b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"a player scores at least 3 in a game.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}